b 2 ,
Figs. 20–21
) long and narrow, expanding slightly at midlength then tapering distad, extending ventrad to level of or even beyond outermost point of process, crossing opposite member in situ ; distal margin of acropodite prolonged into two branches thereby constituting true distal zone, extending ventrad beyond origin of solenomere ( s,
Figs. 20, 21
